# Cost model — DBUs, autoscaling, auto-termination

- DBU (Databricks Unit) — the normalized unit of compute Databricks bills per hour
- Total cost = DBUs + underlying cloud VM cost (bundled for serverless)
- DBU rate varies by workload — job clusters are cheaper than all-purpose
- Autoscaling — add/remove workers between min & max to match load
- Auto-termination — idle clusters shut down after N minutes; serverless scales to zero
